lender.occupational_info: ROAM, or remote operations asset management, is a revolutionary technology that offers new wireless light control. It is a solution to the need for reliability of utility and for safety, security and visual acuity. It allows lighting system managers and operators to quickly detect, repair and manage problems with the lighting systems. ROAM functions by creating a mesh network throughout all the lighting products in a system. With a photocontrol that is embedded with a wireless communication chip for each lighting fixture, errors can easily be communicated and located. Also, key fixture attributes like lamp type and wattage is captured for easy monitoring and management. With ROAM, you can maximize material utilization, reduce energy consumption and increase customer satisfaction. It has already enhanced a number of lighting applications with its wireless light control and holds the “Best of Category” award from the LIGHTFAIR 2007.
